<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-08 12:31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nasdaq Falls 81; Dow Sheds 59  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Blue chip and technology stocks tumbled Friday
as anxious investors sought to take profits in the face of more
corporate earnings warnings.
</P>
<P>
   In midday trading on Wall Street, the Dow Jones industrial
average was down 58.83 at 11,201.04.
</P>
<P>
   The Nasdaq composite index was down 80.79 at 4,017.56, nearly
erasing its 85.01-point gain Thursday. The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500
index fell 9.36 to 1,493.15.
</P>
<P>
   ''What we're doing now is pricing in some measure of an economic
slowdown. We're looking at a fair number of warnings about
slowdowns in the third quarter,'' said Chris Dickerson, an analyst
with Global Market Strategists in Gainesville, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   Before the market opened, a handful of companies warned that
their earnings would not meet expectations, including automotive
parts maker TRW, whose stock fell $1.63 to $43.63 on the New York
Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
   A warning from Gadzoox Networks pushed its shares down $1.88 --
or more than 18 percent -- to $8.44 on the Nasdaq.
</P>
<P>
   Shares of First Data dropped $3.94 to $39.75, a 9 percent change
after an analyst downgraded the credit-card transaction processor's
stock to ''outperform'' from ''strong buy.''
</P>
<P>
   On Thursday, the Dow fell 50.77 after chemical company DuPont
warned that its earnings would be down because of soft demand and
increased costs.
</P>
<P>
   Earlier in the week, investors had bid blue chips higher.
</P>
<P>
   Dickerson, the analyst, said the market's focus on tech stocks
one day, then blue chips another reflects its lack of direction -- a
listlessness which makes life difficult for investors and money
managers.
</P>
<P>
   ''Anytime anything looks to be moving, money mangers jump into
that sector because they have to squeeze out what percentage of
profit they can. They'll jump in for a couple of days and then jump
out,'' he said. ''There's a rush almost to avoid not losing out.''
</P>
<P>
   The Russell 2000 index was down 4.62 at 538.20.
</P>
<P>
   Declining issues outnumbered advancers by about a 5-to-4 margin
on the New York Stock Exchange, where volume came to 452.11 million
shares, compared to 450.77 million the previous session.
</P>
<P>
