<HEADLINE> 30 Die in Indian Boat Accident  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LUCKNOW, India (AP) -- An overcrowded boat capsized Friday in a
river in India's most populous state, drowning at least 30 people,
police said.
</P>
<P>
   The boat overturned in the Pilakhar River near Pashpura village
in northern Uttar Pradesh state, police spokesman O.P. Mani
Tripathi said. The area is 105 miles east of India's capital, New
Delhi.
</P>
<P>
   Many villagers across India use boats as public transport in
remote areas. Scores of people are often crammed into large
vessels, and with lax safety laws, many drownings occur each year.
</P>
