<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-08 16:25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> $adv10  </HEADLINE>
By TIMOTHY WILLIAMS
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) - At first, her public appearances were furtive
and mayoral aides lied about who she was. Then, as her relationship
with Mayor Rudolph Giuliani threatened to explode into scandal, she
disappeared from public view.
</P>
<P>
   But now, with the lame duck mayor's second term winding down,
Judith Nathan has taken an increasingly high public profile,
performing functions formerly carried out by Donna Hanover,
Giuliani's wife, and the city's official first lady.
</P>
<P>
   At the inauguration of new Police Commissioner Bernard Kerik
last week, there was Nathan - not Hanover- front row center,
snapping pictures with a small silver camera and nodding
encouragingly as the mayor spoke.
</P>
<P>
   A few days before, the 45-year-old pharmaceutical company
executive marched alongside the mayor at the city's West Indian Day
Parade, decked out in a big straw hat and white shirt casually
knotted at the midriff. She beamed, joked with the mayor, waved to
the crowd.
</P>
<P>
   And there she was at the Republican National Convention, at a
fundraiser for Rep. Rick Lazio, marching in a Fourth of July parade
on Staten Island - increasingly taking on the role of First Lady of
New York.
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile, Hanover -Giuliani's wife of 16 years and the mother
of his two children - has been conspicuously absent from most
official events.
</P>
<P>
   ''Of course this is very hurtful, but Donna is acting with
enormous grace and dignity, taking care of her children and
continuing her First Lady work for various New York City
charities,'' Hanover spokeswoman Joannie Danielides said this week.
</P>
<P>
   Hanover, 50, a television personality and actress, has publicly
accused her husband of not only cheating with Nathan, but also of
having an affair with former mayoral aide Cristyne
Lategano-Nicholas. Both Giuliani and Lategano-Nicholas have denied
having an affair.
</P>
<P>
   While Hanover has hired a divorce lawyer, Giuliani has not,
though he has said that he is seeking a legal separation - which he
took pains to point out this spring is not the same as a divorce.
</P>
<P>
   Observers say that Giuliani, 56, is able to flaunt his
relationship with Nathan, who he has described as his ''very good
friend,'' without much complaint for two reasons: He has only 14
months left in office, and the public is still grateful to him for
the city's chugging economy and precipitous drop in crime.
</P>
<P>
   ''This is an unintended consequence of term limits,'' said
Maurice Carroll, director of the Quinnipiac College Polling
Institute. ''Anyone who was running for election wouldn't be doing
that.''
</P>
<P>
   When the Republican Giuliani dropped out of a race for the U.S.
Senate against first lady Hillary Rodham Clinton in May, he cited
his prostate cancer, not his marriage woes as the reason.
</P>
<P>
   But Republican political consultant Jay Severin said President
Clinton's relationship with White House intern Monica Lewinsky has
changed the landscape, and since then, the public has affected a
live-and-let-live attitude about the moral shortcomings of its
politicians.
</P>
<P>
   ''Both the public display and the public reaction to this is
extraordinary,'' said Severin. ''The fact that he can do this is
scandalous, but there is no scandal, ipso facto, it must not be
scandalous.''
</P>
<P>
   Columbia University public policy professor Steven Cohen said
public expectations of its leaders have evolved over a short period
of time.
</P>
<P>
   ''People are sophisticated enough to separate the personal from
the professional where they can now say, 'He's a pretty good public
official, but I wouldn't want to have dinner with him.'''
</P>
<P>
   For now, Nathan has become just another character in the fabric
of the city's life - a far cry from the days not-too-long ago when
she marched anonymously behind the mayor in parades, and Giuliani
aides told reporters that she was a friend of various mayoral
aides.
</P>
<P>
   So what does the future hold for the couple?
</P>
<P>
   Manos Zacharioudakis, who lived with Nathan and her 15-year-old
daughter in Manhattan before Nathan started seeing Giuliani last
year, has an idea.
</P>
<P>
   ''If there is going to be a next Mrs. Giuliani,'' he said, ''she
is going to make a perfect wife. She is an extraordinary
individual.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-ES-09-08-00 1625 </TRAILER>
</DOC>
