<HEADLINE> Garfield public works chief charged with stealing from police headquarters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   GARFIELD, N.J. (AP) - The borough's public works superintendent
is accused of stealing money from a locked desk at police
headquarters.
</P>
<P>
   Bergen County Prosecutor William H. Schmidt said John DePeri,
52, of Maywood was secretly videotaped while breaking into a locked
desk inside police headquarters on Wednesday and taking $100 in
cash.
</P>
<P>
   Police had set up a hidden camera in the office where the thefts
occurred after the first two incidents occurred on Aug. 11 and 15.
</P>
