<HEADLINE> Man runs on Field at Cubs Game  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   CHICAGO (AP) -- A man ran on the field at Wrigley Field in the
seventh inning Friday, stripped, stood on the mound and made an
obscene gesture.
</P>
<P>
   The Chicago Cubs' Eric Young had just singled to lead off the
seventh when James Short, 43, of Deerfield, Ill., ran onto the
field from near the visiting team's dugout. Short stopped shy of
the mound, took off his shorts and shirt, and then stood on the
mound.
</P>
<P>
   Chicago's Ricky Gutierrez, who was at the plate, was seen
laughing along with several other players.
</P>
<P>
   Short was taken away by security guards, who grabbed him by his
hair and rushed him off the field and through the stands, still
naked. He was charged with criminal trespass and indecent exposure,
a Chicago police spokesman said.
</P>
</TEXT>
