<HEADLINE> New Jersey establishes trade agreement with Greece  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   TRENTON, N.J. (AP) - New Jersey has a new trading partner.
</P>
<P>
   State officials announced Friday that New Jersey is the first
state to establish a trade representative in Greece.
</P>
<P>
   The state Commerce &AMP; Economic Growth Commission agreed to deal
with officials with American-Hellenic Chamber of Commerce, a
leading Greece business organization headquartered in Athens.
</P>
<P>
   Under the agreement, the chamber will function as the
commission's official representative in the country, promoting
increased trade between Greece and the state and the New Jersey
businesses.
</P>
<P>
   With more than $22.7 billion in goods shipped around the world,
New Jersey ranks ninth in exports in the nation.
</P>
<P>
   The state maintains a trade presence in Japan, England, Mexico,
Israel and Egypt.
</P>
</TEXT>
