<HEADLINE> Spicy Stuff Wins at Del Mar  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   DEL MAR, Calif. (AP) -- Spicy Stuff beat Contexte by 2&AMP;frac12; lengths
Friday in the featured $81,000 El Cajon Stakes at Del Mar.
</P>
<P>
   Kentucky-bred Spicy Stuff, ridden by Victor Espinoza, led the
field of seven and finished the one-mile race for three-year olds
in 1:37 1-5. The 2-1 favorite, carrying 122 pounds, returned $3.00,
$2.20 and $2.10.
</P>
<P>
   Spicy Stuff, a son of Tabasco Cat trained by Bob Baffert, earned
$47,250 with his third win in nine starts.
</P>
<P>
   Contexte, with Alex Solis aboard and carrying 115 pounds, was
second, a half-length in front of Cozy Man and jockey Martin
Pedroza. He paid $2.60 and $2.20.
</P>
<P>
   Cozy Man also carried 115 pounds and paid $2.40 to show.
</P>
<P>
   Espinoza also won the second race on Go for Puddin, the third on
Sudden Glory and the fifth on Racene.
</P>
</TEXT>
